rates that, under the given physical parameters (conductivity, film thickness, frequency range), the `reflection_coefficient` function (Liu et al. Eq. 5) does not exhibit the necessary topological features (zeros, poles, or phase dislocations) that would lead to a non-zero winding number or a $\\pi$ phase jump. This implies that either the chosen parameters are not within the topological regime predicted by Liu et al., or the interpretation of the topological features in this specific model needs further clarification from the original source material. The system appears to behave classically, with no detected topological invariants of the type expected.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"b3c5fd5b"},"source":["## Detailed Analysis of Phase Jump and Z₂ Berry Phase\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Perform a high-resolution plot of `np.angle(r)` versus `theta` specifically around the pseudo-Brewster angle (`theta_c_deg`) to precisely measure any phase jump. Additionally, plot `np.imag(r)` and `np.real(r)` to visually confirm if `r` crosses the origin or the negative real axis, which would signify a topological phase jump. Re-evaluate the `compute_berry_phase_z2` function with a clearer theoretical justification for the expected π/2 value in lossy systems, or adjust the calculation if an alternative interpretation of Z₂ Berry phase (e.g., π) is more appropriate for this specific model.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"dbe064e2"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","The subtask requires a high-resolution plot of the reflection phase, visualization of the complex reflection coefficient path, recalculation of the phase jump, and re-evaluation of the Z2 Berry phase. All these calculations and visualizations are directly related to understanding the phase behavior around the pseudo-Brewster angle. Therefore, I will implement them in a single code block.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":465},"id":"2ee6500d","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1769927129080,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":1287,"user":{"displayName":"Will Lenchus","userId":"03870594209213912784"}},"outputId":"1a6326dc-e962-423c-9a3b-78b9f69d4522"},"source":["import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# --- Parameters and functions from previous cells ---\n","# Ensure these are defined if running this cell standalone\n","eps0 = 8.854e-12      # Permittivity of vacuum [F/m]\n","mu0 = 4*np.pi*1e-7    # Permeability of vacuum [H/m]\n","c = 1/np.sqrt(eps0*mu0)\n","\n","def reflection_coefficient(omega, theta_deg, sigma, d_f):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Implements Liu et al. Eq. (5) for ultrathin conductive film.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    theta = np.deg2rad(theta_deg)\n","    beta = sigma * omega * mu0 * d_f**2\n","    gamma = np.sqrt(sigma / (omega * eps0)) * np.cos(theta)\n","    sqrt_i = np.exp(1j * np.pi/4)\n","    sqrt_i_beta = np.sqrt(1j * beta)\n","    numerator = - (1j + gamma**2) * np.sin(sqrt_i_beta)\n","    denominator = (2 * sqrt_i * gamma * np.cos(sqrt_i_beta) +\n","                   (-1j + gamma**2) * np.sin(sqrt_i_beta))\n","    r = numerator / denominator\n","    return r\n","\n","def compute_berry_phase_z2(omega_fixed, theta_path, sigma, d_f):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Compute Berry phase modulo pi (valid for lossy systems).\n","    The HBAR wall corresponds to a pi-phase jump (Z_2 charge).\n","    \"\"\"\n","    phases = np.array([np.angle(reflection_coefficient(omega_fixed, t, sigma, d_f))\n","                       for t in theta_path])\n","    # Unwrap modulo pi (not 2pi) for lossy systems\n","    # This is a conceptual unwrapping to see if large jumps occur.\n","    # For robust Z2, typically look for sign changes or specific winding.\n","\n","    # For a Z2 Berry phase, one typically looks for a Pi jump in the phase\n","    # or a change in the sign of an eigenvalue etc. The modulo pi unwrapping\n","    # can highlight this if the phase itself jumps by pi. Given our earlier\n","    # observation of smooth phase, this might not yield the expected pi/2 or pi.\n","\n","    # Let's try unwrapping then taking diff modulo pi to directly see the jumps.\n","    unwrapped_phases = np.unwrap(phases)\n","    diff_phases = np.diff(unwrapped_phases)\n","\n","    # Sum of differences modulo pi, then take modulo pi again for the total phase\n","    total_berry_phase = np.mod(np.sum(diff_phases), np.pi)\n","\n","    return total_berry_phase\n","\n","\n","# Re-define main analysis parameters for clarity\n","f0 = 0.3e12  # 0.3 THz\n","omega0 = 2*np.pi*f0\n","sigma = 1.12e5  # Point P2 conductivity\n","d_f = 10e-6     # Film thickness\n","\n","# Calculate pseudo-Brewster angle\n","theta_c = np.arccos(np.sqrt(omega0 * eps0 / sigma))\n","theta_c_deg = np.rad2deg(theta_c)\n","\n","print(f\"Pseudo-Brewster angle: {theta_c_deg:.2f}°\")\n","\n","# 1. Define a very fine angular grid around theta_c_deg\n","theta_fine_jump = np.linspace(theta_c_deg - 0.1, theta_c_deg + 0.1, 1000)\n","\n","# 2. Calculate the complex reflection coefficients\n","r_fine_jump = np.array([reflection_coefficient(omega0, t, sigma, d_f)\n","                        for t in theta_fine_jump])\n","\n","# 3. Calculate the phase\n","phi_fine_jump = np.angle(r_fine_jump)\n","\n","# 4. Create a plot showing phi_fine_jump versus theta_fine_jump\n","plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n","plt.plot(theta_fine_jump, phi_fine_jump, 'b-')\n","plt.axvline(theta_c_deg, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Pseudo-Brewster Angle ({theta_c_deg:.2f}°)')\n","plt.xlabel('Incident Angle θ (degrees)')\n","plt.ylabel('Reflection Phase φ (radians)')\n","plt.title('High-Resolution Reflection Phase around Pseudo-Brewster Angle')\n","plt.grid(True)\n","plt.legend()\n","plt.savefig('high_res_phase_jump.png', dpi=150)\n","plt.show()\n","\n","# 6. Re-calculate the phase jump delta_phi\n","# Find indices just below and just above theta_c_deg\n","idx_below = np.argmin(np.abs(theta_fine_jump - (theta_c_deg - 0.001)))\n","idx_above = np.argmin(np.abs(theta_fine_jump - (theta_c_deg + 0.001)))\n","\n","phi_at_below = np.angle(reflection_coefficient(omega0, theta_fine_jump[idx_below], sigma, d_f))\n","phi_at_above = np.angle(reflection_coefficient(omega0, theta_fine_jump[idx_above], sigma, d_f))\n","\n","delta_phi = phi_at_above - phi_at_below\n","# Correct for 2pi periodicity if needed to get shortest phase difference\n","delta_phi_wrapped = np.arctan2(np.sin(delta_phi), np.cos(delta_phi))\n","\n","# 7. Print the calculated delta_phi\n","print(f\"\\nPhase jump (delta_phi) across pseudo-Brewster angle: {delta_phi_wrapped:.4f} radians (Expected: ~pi or ~0)\")\n","\n","# 8. Re-run the compute_berry_phase_z2 function\n","berry_z2_recalc = compute_berry_phase_z2(omega0, theta_fine_jump, sigma, d_f)\n","\n","# 9. Print the result of the compute_berry_phase_z2 function\n","print(f\"Z2 Berry phase (recalculated): {berry_z2_recalc:.4f} radians (Expected: pi/2 or pi for topological features)\")\n","\n","# 10. Plot np.real(r_fine_jump) vs np.imag(r_fine_jump)\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n","plt.plot(np.real(r_fine_jump), np.imag(r_fine_jump), 'm-', label='r(θ) path')\n","plt.scatter(np.real(r_fine_jump[::50]), np.imag(r_fine_jump[::50]), color='purple', s=20, zorder=5, label='Sampled Points')\n","plt.axhline(0, color='k', linestyle=':', linewidth=0.7)\n","plt.axvline(0, color='k', linestyle=':', linewidth=0.7)\n","plt.plot(0, 0, 'rx', markersize=10, mew=2, label='Origin (0,0)')\n","plt.xlabel('Real(r)')\n","plt.ylabel('Imag(r)')\n","plt.title(f'Complex Reflection Coefficient r(θ) Path at ω = {f0/1e12:.2f} THz (High-Res)')\n","plt.grid(True)\n","plt.axis('equal') # Ensure aspect ratio is 1:1\n","plt.legend()\n","plt.savefig('high_res_r_complex_path.png', dpi=150)\n","plt.show()"],"execution_count":57,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Pseudo-Brewster angle: 89.30°\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x600 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"}